<div id="outline-container-orge2dbff6" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="orge2dbff6"><span class="section-number-2">6.</span> ECN vs. STP</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-6">
<table border="2" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="6" rules="groups" frame="hsides">


<colgroup>
<col  class="org-left" />

<col  class="org-left" />

<col  class="org-left" />
</colgroup>
<thead>
<tr>
<th scope="col" class="org-left">&#xa0;</th>
<th scope="col" class="org-left">ECN Brokers</th>
<th scope="col" class="org-left">STP Brokers</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class="org-left">Order routing</td>
<td class="org-left">Order is routed straight through to the central interbank market</td>
<td class="org-left">Order is routed directly to a counterparty that might be the interbank market,</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td class="org-left">&#xa0;</td>
<td class="org-left">and is filled at the best market rate with no dealer intervention.</td>
<td class="org-left">another STP broker, a market maker, or even an ECN broker.</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td class="org-left">&#xa0;</td>
<td class="org-left">&#xa0;</td>
<td class="org-left">&#xa0;</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td class="org-left">Speed of execution</td>
<td class="org-left">An ECN broker executes trades over the ECN for potential investors,</td>
<td class="org-left">The Speed of execution depends on the exact route it takes on specific orders.</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td class="org-left">&#xa0;</td>
<td class="org-left">which results in the lowest execution time.</td>
<td class="org-left">&#xa0;</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td class="org-left">&#xa0;</td>
<td class="org-left">&#xa0;</td>
<td class="org-left">&#xa0;</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td class="org-left">Fee structure</td>
<td class="org-left">Always charges a small commission for trades and always has variable spreads.</td>
<td class="org-left">Can charge commissions and also earn from the spreads. STP can offer variable and fixed spreads.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>


