<div id="outline-container-org1ede3c4" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org1ede3c4"><span class="section-number-2">27.</span> LULD</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-27">

<div id="org565e025" class="figure">
<p><img src="./LULDFlow.png" alt="LULDFlow.png" />
</p>
</div>
</div>


<div id="outline-container-orge60d709" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="orge60d709"><span class="section-number-3">27.1.</span> Reference Price and Bands Determination:</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-27-1">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>The exchange calculates the reference price, which is the five-minute moving average of the security's last sales price.</li>
<li>LULD bands are set based on the reference price:</li>
</ul>
<p>
&#x2013; For Tier 1 securities (e.g., S&amp;P 500), the bands are 5% (10% at open/close).
&#x2013; For Tier 2 securities (all other NMS stocks), the bands are 10% (20% at open/close).
&#x2013; For securities priced under $0.75, the bands are the lesser of $0.15 or 75% (doubled at open/close).
</p>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org3b60611" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org3b60611"><span class="section-number-3">27.2.</span> Limit State:</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-27-2">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>If a quote is entered that moves the national best offer price to the lower band or the national best bid price to the upper band without crossing the market, a 15-second limit state begins.</li>
<li>Trading can continue within the band during this time.</li>
<li>The limit state ends if the quote causing it is executed, canceled, or modified.</li>
<li>If the national best bid or offer remains at the band for 15 seconds, a five-minute trading halt begins.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org019a7db" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org019a7db"><span class="section-number-3">27.3.</span> LULD Halts Sequence:</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-27-3">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>An initial halt occurs if a security enters a limit state.</li>
<li>During the five-minute volatility trading pause, no trading may occur, but quotes can be updated, and orders can be accepted.</li>
<li>The halt can end after the mandatory five minutes when the primary market reports a re-opening price.</li>
<li>If the issue causing the halt is not resolved, subsequent halts may occur in response to further limit state triggers.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org5fa9dfb" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org5fa9dfb"><span class="section-number-3">27.4.</span> Subsequent Halts:</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-27-4">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>If the same issue persists and triggers another limit state after the initial halt ends, a new five-minute trading halt begins.</li>
<li>Subsequent halts can repeat if the issue continues.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-orgee60c75" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="orgee60c75"><span class="section-number-3">27.5.</span> Conclusion If Not Resolved:</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-27-5">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>If the issue causing the halt is not resolved after multiple halts, the security may remain halted for an extended period.</li>
<li>The exchange, in conjunction with regulatory bodies like the SEC, may investigate the issue and determine appropriate actions to resolve it.</li>
</ul>





<div id="org23db3dd" class="figure">
<p><img src="./LULD.png" alt="LULD.png" />
</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>


<div id="outline-container-org7124804" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org7124804"><span class="section-number-2">28.</span> Straddle State</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-28">
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org3df461f" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org3df461f"><span class="section-number-3">28.1.</span> Under LULD, a security is in a straddle state if the bid and offer are on either side of the price band.</h3>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org64127d1" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org64127d1"><span class="section-number-3">28.2.</span> Under a straddle state, the exchange will monitor conditions and implement a pause for anything abnormal.</h3>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org6aeb9ee" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org6aeb9ee"><span class="section-number-3">28.3.</span> Example:</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-28-3">
<p>
The reference price for an S&amp;P 500 stock is $50.
Therefore, the 5% band is down to 47.50 and up to 52.50.
If the NBBO is 52.45–.55, this is a straddle state.
</p>



<p>
Numerical Guidelines         Reference Price 	(% Difference from Reference Price) 
</p>

<p>
$0.9999 and under 	         20% 
</p>

<p>
$1–$4.9999 	                 Low end of band: 20%
			     High end of band: 10% 
</p>

<p>
$5–$74.9999 	               10% 
</p>

<p>
$75–$199.9999 	             Low end of band: 10%
			     High end of band: 5% 
$200–$499.9999 	             5%
</p>

<p>
$500–$999.9999 	             Low end of band: 5%
			     High end of band: 3% 
</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-orga78aea6" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="orga78aea6"><span class="section-number-2">29.</span> Short Sell</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-29">
</div>
<div id="outline-container-orgd758a54" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="orgd758a54"><span class="section-number-3">29.1.</span> Broker Dealer</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-29-1">
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org728dc39" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="org728dc39"><span class="section-number-4">29.1.1.</span> Locate</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-29-1-1">
</div>
<ol class="org-ol">
<li><a id="org96f7e40"></a>Agreement with institutional investors<br />
<div class="outline-text-5" id="text-29-1-1-1">
<p>
or
</p>
</div>
</li>
<li><a id="org8fdbc99"></a>Have availability<br />
<ol class="org-ol">
<li><a id="org3e523f3"></a>Should publish the list of available list and update every 24 hours.<br /></li>
</ol>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-orgcf3794d" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="orgcf3794d"><span class="section-number-4">29.1.2.</span> Aggregate the position</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-29-1-2">
</div>
<ol class="org-ol">
<li><a id="org5c51868"></a>real time<br /></li>
<li><a id="org8856cd3"></a>Avoid real time by independent unit aggregation; every unit / Trader will aggregate and will work independently for a specific unit (not more than one unit)<br /></li>
</ol>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org9074785" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="org9074785"><span class="section-number-4">29.1.3.</span> Reporting</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-29-1-3">
</div>
<ol class="org-ol">
<li><a id="org3d53ebb"></a>every 15 days<br /></li>
<li><a id="org9ec5ee5"></a>due 2 days ( 15 + 2 )<br /></li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org7ab0715" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org7ab0715"><span class="section-number-3">29.2.</span> Restrictions</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-29-2">
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org3adf5f2" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="org3adf5f2"><span class="section-number-4">29.2.1.</span> IF market goes down by 10% or more.</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-29-2-1">
</div>
<ol class="org-ol">
<li><a id="org8b3e34e"></a>SS is restricted.<br /></li>
<li><a id="orge6c2b45"></a>trade halt for that day and next day<br /></li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org5fe81ce" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org5fe81ce"><span class="section-number-3">29.3.</span> Restriction exceptions</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-29-3">
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org5c42727" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="org5c42727"><span class="section-number-4">29.3.1.</span> If the if price  higher than the NBB  (e.g. NBB 75.25-50 =&gt; SS 75.26) .</h4>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-orgc28327c" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="orgc28327c"><span class="section-number-4">29.3.2.</span> if long</h4>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-orgbbcdbaf" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="orgbbcdbaf"><span class="section-number-4">29.3.3.</span> If odd lot/warrant/right/covertible/vwap/riskless principal trade/recently traded and will settle next day.</h4>
</div>
</div>

